abstract: The company pushed back its stock offering, reportedly after investors remained cool to the deal. It’s another blow to the business.
snippet: The company pushed back its stock offering, reportedly after investors remained cool to the deal. It’s another blow to the business.
lead_paragraph: Good Tuesday morning. Last night, Steve Schwarzman of Blackstone shared his insights on the U.S.-China trade war — and why he’s worried about the long-term effects of it dragging on. More below. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: An I.P.O. of WeWork Will Have to Wait

abstract: The weekend’s attacks on plants owned by Saudi Arabia’s state-owned oil company spooked investors this morning — and may do so for a long time to come.
snippet: The weekend’s attacks on plants owned by Saudi Arabia’s state-owned oil company spooked investors this morning — and may do so for a long time to come.
lead_paragraph: Good Monday morning. Updates from the Saudi government on the Aramco plants that were attacked could help determine whether the country will move forward with an I.P.O. for the state-owned oil giant. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

abstract: The state would become the second in the nation, behind Michigan, to outlaw sale of the fruity flavors popular with children and teenagers.
snippet: The state would become the second in the nation, behind Michigan, to outlaw sale of the fruity flavors popular with children and teenagers.
lead_paragraph: Amid a surge of vaping-related illnesses and deaths, Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo of New York announced on Sunday that he would pursue emergency regulations this week to quickly ban the sale of flavored e-cigarettes.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Beijing’s Plan to Get to a Trade Deal

abstract: The heads of 145 companies sent a letter to Senate leaders calling for an expansion of background checks to firearms sales and stronger gun laws.
snippet: The heads of 145 companies sent a letter to Senate leaders calling for an expansion of background checks to firearms sales and stronger gun laws.
lead_paragraph: Good Thursday morning. I’m in Washington this afternoon for the DealBook D.C. Summit, where other NYT journalists and I will talk with business and policy leaders about trade, antitrust and more. You can watch my interview with Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin at 5 p.m. Eastern here. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: C.E.O.s Demand More Gun Control

abstract: “Doing nothing about America’s gun violence crisis is simply unacceptable,” the corporate chiefs urged senators in a letter.
snippet: “Doing nothing about America’s gun violence crisis is simply unacceptable,” the corporate chiefs urged senators in a letter.
lead_paragraph: In a direct and urgent call to address gun violence in America, the chief executives of some of the nation’s best-known companies sent a letter to Senate leaders on Thursday, urging an expansion of background checks to all firearms sales and stronger “red flag” laws.

abstract: As vaping-related illnesses spread, President Trump and top health officials met at the White House to discuss ways to keep the products away from teenagers.
snippet: As vaping-related illnesses spread, President Trump and top health officials met at the White House to discuss ways to keep the products away from teenagers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration said on Wednesday that it would ban the sale of most flavored e-cigarettes, at a time when hundreds of people have been sickened by mysterious lung illnesses and teenage vaping continues to rise.
